To make the graph, we'll scale the -axis in multiples of \dfrac{\pi}{6}. We plot the guide points (x,y) from the table, and sketch a sinusoidal graph through the points. One cycle of the graph is shown below. As we expected,the graph is shifted \dfrac{\pi}{3} units to the left compared to the graph of y = \cos x.


